  <sec>
    <title>Results and discussion</title>
    <p>Several new features have been implemented in version 2.0. The main enhancements deal with analyzing time-course multiple-level data through: (a) changes in gene expression, protein concentration or other parameters tracked through color changes; (b) clustering of entities on different layers based on associated values; (c) individual gene tracking; (d) display of gene correlations; (e) scoring and coloring based on similarity features. The color scheme used for tracking time-resolved changes or for similarity depiction can be changed according to the user's wish, including gradients visible for colorblind people. A more detailed listing of the new features can be found in Table <xref ref-type="table" rid="T1">1</xref>. These can be accessed within the application as described in Figure <xref ref-type="fig" rid="F1">1</xref>.</p>
